### DECISION_REVIEW

`[R-018-D1] AGREE — three separate packets (009/010/011) — reasoning: 009 = RUNTIME DISCIPLINE (agent prompts/completion gate/CLAUDE.md; T5–T9, 5 phase children), 010 = TEST INFRASTRUCTURE (deep-improvement Lane B; no shipped feature), 011 = NEW VALIDATION RULE (AC coverage; ERROR-severity capable). These three are orthogonal surfaces with no conceptual overlap; merging 011 into 009 would push 009 past 10 phase children and couple a validator-rule blast radius (011) with a discipline-bundle change (009) — proposal §1/§2/§3 + spec.md:131 explicitly keeps T1 unowned. Verified surface disjointness in 001/spec.md:91 (templates only), 002-008 (mcp_server/handlers + lib/*) — proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:31, 51, 71.`

`[R-018-D2] AGREE — 009/010/011 numbering — reasoning: 027 top-level has 000–008 occupied (ls of 027/ shows 000-release-cleanup through 008-learning-feedback-reducers). 000 is flagged "Placeholder" in spec.md:130 and explicitly called out in spec.md:180 ("remain a placeholder indefinitely…?"). 008 children are 001/003/004/005 (no 002 — coco deleted, gap preserved per 005/research.md:58). 009 is the next legal number, and the proposal correctly avoids the 000 placeholder and the 008/002 coco gap — proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:25.`

`[R-018-D3] AGREE — 010 (benchmark substrate) FIRST — reasoning: 010 has zero structural deps (lane B already exists at `.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/` with `benchmark-fixtures/`, `benchmark-profiles/`, `scripts/model-benchmark/{run-benchmark,sweep-benchmark,dispatch-model}.cjs` per deep-improvement/SKILL.md:32-356), it ships no user-visible rule (only a schema extension + scorer + fixture dir), and 009/011 each want regression fixtures. Caveat (proposal already acknowledges at line 100 "operator decision"): 010-first is a recommendation, not a hard gate — if 010's fixture schema proves wrong, re-shaping is cheap since it ships no behavior. proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:48-53.`

`[R-018-D4] AGREE — fold T14/T12 into PENDING 001/003 and 001/004 — reasoning: 001/spec.md:107-108 shows pending 001/003 (T4 current-state discipline) and 001/004 (T2 constitutional rule review) are Planned, not yet implemented. T14 (current-state generalization to implementation-summary.md + product.md narrative) is a direct extension of 001/003's surface (current-state discipline); T12 (bounded cap + recurrence→promotion) is a direct extension of 001/004's surface (constitutional review). Folding avoids editing the same surfaces twice once 001/003 and 001/004 ship — proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:77-80. The DEFERs (T14's non-parent spec.md generalization, T12(c) prune-lifecycle) are good judgment — 006/research.md:88-90, 010 (high false-positive / high-risk).`

`[R-018-D5] AGREE — T1 as its OWN packet (011) vs sub-phase of 009 — reasoning: T1 (AC coverage gate) has 5 phase children of its own (AC-format prereq, AC traceability table, AC_COVERAGE rule, deep-review verdict binding, ERROR promotion) per proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:64-69. 011's ERROR rule can block in-flight L2+ folders (mitigated by warn-only adoption window + per-level opt-in, proposal line 70-71). 009's 5 phase children (T6/T5/T7/T8/T9) are already at the comfortable upper limit. T1 is unowned: 027/spec.md:102 ("Implementing the peck-derived T1 per-acceptance-criterion coverage gate" is Out-of-Scope) and 001/spec.md:83 (T1 explicitly excluded). Merging into 009 would conflate validator-rule blast radius with discipline-bundle change — proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:59-60.`

`[R-018-D6] REFINE — sequencing independence claim is correct for the 002-008 memory axis, but the §7 sequencing diagram understates the coordination needed with PENDING 001/002 (T3 self-check templates) — reasoning: 011 phase 001 (AC-format normalization, `templates/manifest/spec.md.tmpl`) and 011 phase 002 (AC traceability table, `templates/manifest/checklist.md.tmpl`) both touch the same manifest templates that 001/spec.md:91 puts in 001/002's scope ("templates/manifest/{spec,plan,checklist}.md.tmpl — Modify 002 — Self-check + failure-mode guidance blocks"). The proposal text at proposal/sub-packet-proposal.md:64 and 71 acknowledges this ("Coordinate with pending 002-self-check-templates"), and the 005/research.md:120 re-plan does NOT gate 001/002 ("001 refine folds into Phase 0 docs cleanup" but the implementation sequence is 002‖003→008→004→005→006→007, not touching 001/002). So D6 is structurally correct (009/010/011 do not block on 002-008 memory phases), but the operator needs to see the 001/002 coordination arrow. — Alternative: in proposal §7 sequencing diagram, add a dotted `coordinate w/ 001/002 (T3 templates)` arrow touching 011 phases 001-002; add a one-line note "011 phases 001-002 share manifest templates with pending 001/002; coordinate edit windows or sequence 001/002 first." This is cosmetic but the operator's "next step" decision (proposal line 100) needs the dependency visible.`

### OVERALL
ENDORSE-WITH-CHANGES — decomposition, numbering, level assignment, and dependency analysis are sound; only must-fix is to make the 001/002 (T3 templates) coordination explicit in the §7 sequencing diagram so the operator can plan 011 phases 001-002 against 001/002's edit window. Everything else is endorsement-quality.

